column4: Hi can anyone give me a hand with Virtualbox on Ubuntu 10.4 I cant seem to get a command working, I am trying to use this in terminal "VBoxManage setextradata “VM name” “CustomVideoMode1″ “1280×800×32”
but I get VBoxManage: error: Could not find a registered machine named '“VM name”
any ideas what is wrong ?
Did you type in the correct machine name?
Are you running this on a Server or Desktop?
Can you launch VirtualBox and look at Manager?
What is the name of the VM you are trying to manage on the left?
No spaces or special characters?
What command are you attempting to run?
What output do you get from "VBoxManage list"?
Try your command without the quotes around the machine name...
Can you change the resolution in the actual VM?
Strange...  I can change resolution in a Windows VM.  Haven't done a Mac one.
that's annoying.
That may do it.
how about this I open the MacOSX.vbox in gedit and check the settings it seems the first lot of settings worked in terminal i see the screen resolution i wanted is in the config file...
Hmmm...  are there Vbox extentions that you have to install in MacOSX like there is in Windows?
the extensions I can install for Virtualbox are to allow USB support if i remember right only other thing I can think of is the guest additions which is for windows
you may need to install the guest additions.  I know a video driver gets installed with the Windows version.
ew.
Check out http://www.playonlinux.com/en/
Not at that time.  lol
